      <h2>Risks & What This Model Misses</h2>

      <h3>Upside risks (our number could be too low)</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Margin expansion:</strong> If Precision Scheduled Railroading (PSR) or new automation initiatives drastically improve the operating ratio, cash flows could exceed the 5% growth trend.</li>
        <li><strong>Near-shoring boom:</strong> Increased manufacturing in Mexico directly benefits UNP's network, which connects key border crossings to the US Midwest.</li>
        <li><strong>Share repurchases:</strong> Aggressive buybacks consistently lower the share count, artificially driving per-share value up faster than enterprise growth.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Downside risks (our number could be too high)</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Macroeconomic recession:</strong> Rail volumes are sensitive to industrial, agricultural, and consumer goods spending. A severe recession would crush FCF.</li>
        <li><strong>Labor disputes:</strong> Railroads are highly unionized. Costly contract renegotiations or strikes can severely impact margins.</li>
        <li><strong>Regulatory pressure:</strong> The Surface Transportation Board (STB) heavily regulates railroads and could mandate reciprocal switching or block future rate increases if service quality drops.</li>
      </ul>

